Definition: Source of the distribution map. Could be either "Red List" (if the last range map published in the Red List has been used), "Uploaded" (if the range map was uploaded on the platform), “StoredOnPlatform” (if you used a distribution that was previously createdfrom occurrence records on the platform), or "Created" (if you created a range map from occurrence data)

Source of occurrence data used to create a range map. Could include "GBIF" (automatic download from GBIF website), "OBIS" (automatic download from OBIS website), "Red List" (use of Red List occurrence points), "Uploaded" (upload of your own records)
Species synonyms used to gather occurrence records.
Minimum year of observations. All observations made before this date have been removed from the occurrences
Maximum coordinate uncertainty. All observations with higher localisation uncertainty than this value (in km) will be removed. Only applies to GBIF / OBIS data
Selection of land / sea data. 'excludesea'= Occurrence records made at sea were excluded (Terrestrial species) - 'excludeland'= Occurence records made at land were excluded (Marine species)
Filtering for a geographic extent. Removes observations outside these coordinates (min longitude, max longitude, min latitude, max latitude)
Whether automated filtering (for capitals, zero coordinates, institutions, etc) was run or not
Exclude records with no year information (if equals “TRUE” this means that records with missing information were removed)
Exclude records with no coordinate uncertainty information (if equals “TRUE” this means that records with missing information were removed)

First step of the mapping procedure to create a range map. 'mcp'= Minimum Convex Polygon around occurence records - 'alpha'= Alphahull around occurrence records - 'kernel'= Kernel distribution – ‘indivsites’= Individual sites - 'hydroX'=Hydrobasins of level X with occurrence records - 'hydroMCP= Hydrobasins overlapping with the Minimum Convex Polygon around occurrence records
A buffer of X km has been made around the first range
Has the range been cropped to keep only land or sea. cropland= Only land was kept (sea areas excluded) - cropsea= only sea was kept (land areas excluded)
Minimum and maximum elevation allowed in the range
Merge with published range map (if “TRUE” it means that the distribution created from occurrence records has been merged with the published range map)
Smoothing parameter of the obtained range
Value of the kernel parameter (only important if Kernel has been chosen as the method to map distribution with the Mapping_Start parameter
Value of the Alphahull parameter (only important if Alphahull has been chosen as the method to map distribution with the Mapping_Start parameter
Presence parameters filtered in the Red List or uploaded distribution
Origin parameters filtered in the Red List or uploaded distribution
Seasonal parameters filtered in the Red List or uploaded distribution
Country used to restrict species' distribution in case of National (or European) Red Listing
System preferences selected for the species. Could include terrestrial, freshwater, marine
Habitat preference used to calculate Area of Habitat
Marginal habitat preference used to calculate Area of Habitat (we calculate an AOH without them and one with them to provide the range of AOH)
Elevation preference used to calculate Area of Habitat
Generation Length used to calculate trends in Area of Habitat
Density (mature ind per km2) used to calculate population size

Values entered in the density calculator (either in the AOH or fragmentation step): Density in individuals within occupied habitat / % of mature individuals / % of occupied habitat within suitable habitat / resulting density
Density (mature ind per km2) used to calculate fragmentation
Distance (in km) above which subpopulations are considered isolated
This is the original EOO value calculated by the platform (it might differ from the value in allfields.csv if you manually edited this value)
This is the original AOO value calculated by the platform (it might differ from the value in allfields.csv if you manually edited this value)
This is the original Population Size value calculated by the platform (it might differ from the value in allfields.csv if you manually edited this value)
This is the original Population Trends value calculated by the platform (it might differ from the value in allfields.csv if you manually edited this value)
This is the original direction of Population Trends calculated by the platform (it might differ from the value in allfields.csv if you manually edited this value)
Result of trends in Remote-sensing products (step 6b) for Forest Cover. It includes the current coverage / the absolute trends / the relative trends / the time-window.
Result of trends in Remote-sensing products (step 6b) for Human modification index. It includes the current value / the absolute trends / the relative trends / the time-window.
Result of trends in Remote-sensing products (step 6b) for Human population density. It includes the current value / the absolute trends / the relative trends / the time-window.
Original density estimate suggested by the platform
Original generation length estimate suggested by the platform
